<br>
Here are some problems I see with your charter.<br>
<br>
1.  Commissions being set.  I think each broker should set his own commission rate or perhaps set a payment to owner price (i.e. Owner says get me 100pp, I don't care what you sell for)<br>
<br>
2. Guild fees seem steep.  You are asking capitalistic entreprenuers to join (its their kind of guild) yet you are basing fees on heavy taxes.  <br>
<br>
3.  Guild fees go towards what exactly?.....you never explained that.  What exactly is that paying for.  You made an example of how much the broker can make but geez, just think of what some lucky bastard who is collecting the fees going to make.  Also, how are you going to enforce the reporting and paying of the taxes?<br>
<br>
If I were to do this it would be simple:<br>
1. Guild set up to promote business w/in the world of Norrath.<br>
2. Membership is strictly on an invite basis and members will be upheld to the most extreme principles of fair trade and honesty.  Anyone seeing our guild tag will know they can fully trust said broker, even with selling items between two different characters (ie get cash from main, give item to alt.)<br>
3. Membership is not limited to mains. <br>
4. No fees for belonging to the guild exist as the guild has no costs associated with it.<br>
5. No price wars between members.  No member will sell below a current members auctions when in the same zone.<br>
6. Any changes to the charter must be voted on and accepted by a Quorom (2/3's ) vote.<br>
<br>
Much could be done with a guild of this sort. <p>Herder
